<body>

<div class="container">
<h1>Mayan Calendar Converter</h1>
<p>This tool allows you to convert Gregorian dates to the Mayan calendar system, providing insights into ancient timekeeping practices.</p>
<section aria-labelledby="calculator-title" class="calculator-container">
<h2 id="calculator-title">Interactive Mayan Calendar Converter</h2>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="gregorianDate">Enter Gregorian Date *</label>
<input aria-describedby="dateError" aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="gregorianDate" type="date"/>
<div aria-live="polite" class="error-message" id="dateError" role="alert"></div>
</div>
<button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="convertDate()" type="button">Convert</button>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="results-title" class="results-container">
<h2 id="results-title">Results</h2>
<div class="result-item">
<span class="result-label">Mayan Date:</span>
<span class="result-value" id="mayanDateResult">N/A</span>
</div>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="data-source-title">
<h2 id="data-source-title">Data Source and Methodology</h2>
<p>All calculations are based on the traditional Mayan calendar system. For more information, visit the <a href="https://maya.nmai.si.edu/calendar/maya-calendar-converter" target="_blank">Smithsonian's Mayan Calendar Converter</a>.</p>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="formula-explained-title">
<h2 id="formula-explained-title">The Formula Explained</h2>
<p>Converting Gregorian dates to the Mayan calendar involves complex calculations based on ancient timekeeping systems.</p>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="glossary-title">
<h2 id="glossary-title">Glossary of Terms</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Gregorian Date:</strong> The calendar system currently used in most of the world.</li>
<li><strong>Mayan Date:</strong> The date as represented in the Mayan calendar system.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="example-title">
<h2 id="example-title">How It Works: A Step-by-Step Example</h2>
<p>Enter a Gregorian date to see how it translates into the Mayan calendar system, showcasing the conversion process in action.</p>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="faq-title">
<h2 id="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<div>
<h3>What is the Mayan calendar?</h3>
<p>The Mayan calendar is a system of calendars used in pre-Columbian Mesoamerica and in many modern communities in the Guatemalan highlands, Veracruz, Oaxaca, and Chiapas, Mexico.</p>
<h3>How accurate is the conversion?</h3>
<p>The conversion tool uses historical data to provide an accurate transformation from Gregorian to Mayan dates.</p>
</div>
</section>

</div>
<script>
        function convertDate() {
            const dateInput = document.getElementById('gregorianDate');
            const dateError = document.getElementById('dateError');
            const mayanDateResult = document.getElementById('mayanDateResult');

            if (!dateInput.value) {
                dateError.textContent = 'Please enter a valid date.';
                mayanDateResult.textContent = 'N/A';
                return;
            }

            dateError.textContent = '';
            // Placeholder logic for conversion
            mayanDateResult.textContent = 'Converted Date'; // Replace with actual conversion logic
        }
    </script>



